5:
Hehe... I saved up enough to treat
myself. I've been wanting my own
ball for a really long time...
10:
Huh? It'd be boring to play by
myself? Well, I have YOU to play with
me!
14:
Okay, you're right. This feels kind of
pointless...
20:
I guess I'll just have to find someone
who wants to play ball with me!
27:
The architecture in this area's a bit
different...
31:
Hey there, little girl. Do you live in the
area? Can you tell me what kind of
place this is?
38:
Hm... For one thing, I'm seeing a lot
of gray.
41:
Are you here just to make a fool of
m—whoa, you look like one of those
rich people.
45:
Rich? Me? I just used up all my
money, so I'm hardly rich!
50:
What are you doing out here all
alone anyway?
58: Hehe, I get it. You must be alone.
61:
What's wrong with that? I just had a
fight with another kid at the
orphanage...
66:
Sounds like somebody's free. Care
to play a game with me?
71:
You know, your eyes really remind
me of my brother's.
74:
You... Never mind... Why are you
even talking to me?
78:
Does it matter? Come with me; I
have something to show you.
85:
Not again... I just hope you're not
dragging her around against her will.
89:
Come to think of it, I don't even know
her name yet, but... I'm sure it'll be
fine!
97:
Talk about déjà vu... Did you have
any activity in mind?
101:
Hehe... You bet I do. I spent my
hard-earned money just for this!
106:
Gah, not again! How could you miss
such an easy shot?!
110:
Um, I probably should've asked
sooner, but why are the teams split
up so that it's you vs. us?
114:
If I had to split my poppets between
the teams, it'd get confusing and I'd
lose track...
120:
Besides, I don't mind being my own
team! I just need one more point to
turn the tables!
124:
And I need YOU to focus! We're
doing this!
133: I noticed you go after every ball...
134:
I'm going to take a wild guess—you
don't actually know the rules, do you?
137:
Pfft—ahahaha! No offense, but you
kind of suck at this, miss!
140:
Hold it right there! Is that a smirk I
see? Grr!
143:
Teehee... Sorry. Thank you so much
for inviting me, miss. I had fun.
148: It's nice to meet you, Saana.
152:
Saana, huh? Pleasure to meet you!
I'm always happy to make another
friend!
157:
You're definitely catching up in the
friends department.
161:
You know, I just thought of
something!
171: Um... Leila, right? From the bridge—
176:
Mm-hm! I though maybe she and
Saana could be friends!
179:
I hope you weren't too pushy about
this, Prika...
180:
I mean, what if she's the type that
prefers to be alone?
184:
Prefers to be alone? There are
people like that? I had no idea...
189:
I hope I didn't come on too hard,
Saana.
192:
Not at all. I just... don't know if many
people would want to be friends
with me...
195:
As long as you're okay with it, let's
play together from now on, Saana.
202: I... didn't mess up, did I?
212:
If you ever do fumble, just figure out
what you did wrong. That's all there
is to it.
215:
Hey, miss. Saana said she wants to
play another round of whatever
game you were playing.
217:
Prika took us all on by herself, even
though she's not the greatest player.
Haha...
220:
You're on! You guys against me
again!
226: I'll win this time for sure!
